==English==
===Noun===
'''slate''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''slates''')

#(''[[uncountable]]'') a fine-grained homogeneous [[sedimentary]] [[rock]] composed of [[clay]] or volcanic ash which has been metamorphosed so that it cleaves easily into thin nayers.
#(''[[uncountable]]'') The [[bluish]]-[[grey]]/[[gray]] [[colour]]/[[color]] of most slate.
#(''[[countable]]'') A sheet of slate for writing on with [[chalk]].
#(''[[countable]]'') A tile made of slate.
#(''[[countable]]'') (''figurative'') A record of [[money]] owed.
#:''Put it on my slate - I'll pay you next week.''
#(''[[countable]]'') A list of [[candidate]]s for an [[election]].

====Synonyms====
*(colour/color): [[slate-grey]], [[slate-gray]]
*(record of money owed): [[account]], [[bill]]

